Experimental principle (i) Convex Hull is a common concept in computational geometry (graphics). In simple terms, given a set of points on a two-dimensional plane, a convex hull is a convex polygon that connects the outermost points to form a polygon that is capable of containing all the points in the point set. One of the more useful ways to understand the shape or corridor of an object is to compute the convex envelope of an object.
(ii) In OpenCV, the convexHull function is used to find the convex packet of an image point set.
